02/04/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A roundtable discussion, titled "Fostering Reconciliation in the Dayton Triangle" was held in Zagreb on Saturday (March 31st), drawing young political leaders and intellectuals from Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia and Serbia. The event was organised and hosted by the Croatian Helsinki Committee. Participants discussed the situation in the region, agreeing that normalising relations among their countries is an irreversible process. They also stressed the importance of establishing the truth about events during the conflicts of the 1990s. (Vecernji list - 01/04/07; HINA - 31/03/07)
